[setup the amplify studio]
1. install nodejs. Go for LTS as they are more stable 
   node --version
2. install visual studio code 

3. In the CI -> sudo npm install -g @aws-amplify/cli #use sudo 

4. login to amplify studio

5. In the CLI -> amplify configure

6. Install git, check for -> git --version
    for the first time user please get the git token & setup the account
    https://docs.github.com/en/enterprise-server@3.4/authentication/keeping-your-account-and-data-secure/creating-a-personal-access-token

7. create a react app -> npx create-react-app breu-score-platform
   sudo npm install -g @aws-amplify/cli
   sudo npm install aws-amplify @aws-amplify/ui-react

8. staging -> amplify pull --appId d3rp29m9hje1ou --envName staging
